theorem Topology.P2_implies_closure_interior_closure_interior_eq_closure_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A →
      closure (interior (closure (interior A))) =
        closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  intro hP2

theorem Topology.closure_interior_closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))))) ⊆
      closure (interior A) := by
  -- We start from the fact that `interior (closure (interior (closure A)))`
  -- is contained in `closure A` (a lemma already in the library).
  have h₁ :
      (interior (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))) : Set X) ⊆ closure A :=
    Topology.interior_closure_interior_subset_closure (A := A)
  -- Since `interior A ⊆ A`, we obtain `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h₂ : (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
    Topology.closure_interior_subset_closure (A := A)
  -- Combining the two inclusions yields the desired result.
  exact closure_mono (Set.Subset.trans h₁ h₂)

theorem Topology.interior_closure_interior_closure_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))) ⊆ closure A := by
  intro x hx
  -- First, upgrade the hypothesis: from the interior we move to the closure.
  have hx' : x ∈ closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) :=
    interior_subset hx
  -- `interior (closure A)` is evidently contained in `closure A`.
  have hInner : (interior (closure (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
    intro y hy
    exact interior_subset hy
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions; simplify the right‐hand side with
  -- `closure_closure`.
  have hClosure :
      (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
    have h := closure_mono hInner
    simpa [closure_closure] using h
  exact hClosure hx'

theorem Topology.frontier_interior_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    frontier (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  -- First, use the general fact `frontier S ⊆ closure S` with `S := interior A`.
  have hx₁ : x ∈ closure (interior (A : Set X)) :=
    (Topology.frontier_subset_closure (A := interior A)) hx
  -- Next, `closure (interior A)` is contained in `closure A`.
  have hsubset : (closure (interior (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ closure A :=
    Topology.closure_interior_subset_closure (A := A)
  -- Combining the two inclusions yields the desired result.
  exact hsubset hx₁
